        <p>We believe churches are stronger when they work together. Over the years we
        have built close partnerships with other congregations in Cathcart, allowing us
        to serve the community more effectively than any of us could do alone.</p>

        {# ── CATHCART CHURCH OF SCOTLAND ── #}
        <div class="section-heading">
            <span class="section-heading-icon" aria-hidden="true">🤝</span>
            <h2>Cathcart Church of Scotland</h2>
            <span class="section-heading-rule" aria-hidden="true"></span>
        </div>

        <div class="card-content-with-image">
            <div>
                <p>We have a covenant partnership with
                <a href="https://www.presbyteryofglasgow.org.uk/churches/cathcart-churchofscotland"
                target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="section-link">Cathcart Church of Scotland</a>
                first signed in 2011 and
                <a href="/life/covenant/" class="section-link">renewed in February 2026</a>.
                This formalises a long-standing relationship of co-operation between the
                two congregations — enabling us to be more effective together than we
                could be working separately.</p>

                <p><strong>Shared activities include:</strong></p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Sunday Evening Services at Cathcart Church of Scotland</li>
                    <li>Wednesday Morning Services at Cathcart United Free Church</li>
                    <li>Small Bible Study groups across both congregations</li>
                    <li>Monthly Prayer Breakfast with Cathcart Baptist Church</li>
                    <li>Holy Week Services rotating across all three Cathcart churches</li>
                    <li>Joint youth ministry through Radiate Cathcart</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="card-image">
                <img src="/assets/images/CovenantSigned.png"
                     alt="Covenant signing service, February 2026"
                     class="content-image-medium" />
            </div>
        </div>

